Instead of conversing the Arlene:
	if HP of Arlene is 0:
		say "     [bold type]BAD PLAYER! You shouldn't be seeing this![roman type]";
	else if HP of Arlene is 1 and cunt count of Player >= 1 and bodyname of Player is "Dragon Breeder" and Player is pure:
		say "     [italic type]Author's note: sections of Arlene's dialogue have been omitted till the next stage of the Cult's development is unlocked to avoid spoilers and confusion.[roman type]";
		Project Figure of Priestess_clothed_icon;
		say "     What do you wish to discuss with your priestess?";
		LineBreak;
		let Scalie_stuff_Choices be a list of text;
		add "Hirself?" to Scalie_stuff_Choices;
		add "Status of Pirate island?" to Scalie_stuff_Choices;
		add "Where is the rest of hir crew?" to Scalie_stuff_Choices;
		add "Just chat?" to Scalie_stuff_Choices;
		let Scalie_stuff_Choice be what the player chooses from Scalie_stuff_Choices;
		if Scalie_stuff_Choice is:
			-- "Hirself?":
				say "     Rightly curious about your hir past, you tactfully inquire how hir life was prior the outbreak, and your meeting on the stricken supply ship. 'Well yar worshipfullness,' shi hums, eyes drifting skywards as shi fidgets beneath your molten gaze, 'dat be a right tough question ta answer. Ya see me memories [']O me self before da troubles be right,' shi pauses, hir tail a twitch with nervous energy,' hazy at times.' No stranger to the mind altering effects of the nanites, you motion for hir to elaborate. '*Cough* so ya see me dragon I'z not sure what'z me, or da crew were in da a old days, or even if we'z was even from dis here berg ta begin with,' shi says, idly gesturing to the city with a soft flick of hir wrist. Really? You ask somewhat perplexed as shi doesn't strike you as either a feral, or some manner of extra dimensional visitor. 'Aya me heart, doe we'z had'z a few [']O dem dare nutter on da account, I'z don't thinks I'z be as far gone as some [']O does loons, but with da Lady's as me witness, I'z not too sure whether I be [']dis place, tar an other, or some pig skin what got changed like da rest,' Arlene says, briefly throwing hir hands up in defeat. But surely shi must remember something of hir past?";
				say "     'Da, I'z getz wee flashes from moon-ta-moon but I'z not sure what be real, or what be a product of dem nanity blighter mess'in wit me mind,' shi sighs dejectedly through a brisk click of hir gleaming fangs. Intrigued, you ask about these flashes of hirs. 'Well,' shi begins eyes drifting towards her desk, 'sometimes I dream [']O me self, or it is me former self,' shi adds, wistfully tapping hir chin, 'sitting at some plain [']ol desk with a screen in front [']O me, and some tiny white keyboard at me finger tips. Try as I'z may, I'z cun never make out what's on it or around me'z, tis like da whole world be made [']O white walls, with a white ceiling, un bathed in white light.' Sounds like a cubical, you rumble offhandly. 'Da mayhaps, doe fir da life of me it could've been an oubliette, fir my thoughts at da time always be of escaping, adventuring, un making me mark. Some-tin be stopping dis [']ere version of me, from leaving dat dare white hell.' Arlene huffs, lips curling into a harsh toothy grimace as shi roughly slams hir tail against the floor with an audible thud.";
				WaitLineBreak;
				say "     'Beyond dat, I'z can'ts tells ya's much whether I'z was a man, woman, short, tall, or any such nonsense, doe I still do be a knowing how the machines [']O dis place works and un some of its history. Ta utter me felt trapped doe, doing the same-tin over un over like some kind [']O right proper nutter. Den,' shi beams, hir expression lightening as shi wistfully peers down at hir [if libido of Arlene is 0]sleek selachian figure [else if libido of Arlene >= 1 and Libido of Arlene < 12]cute curvy bump[else]glorious maternal figure[end if]. 'Dare be time I see me self as I'z am now, da captain [']O some grand crew trawling da deep black [']O some vast zunless sea, pillaging ta waters for all manner of trinkets un baubles for patrons too vast un unknowable to describe. Un doe we was free to live as we chose, we'z was hunted, un hated by all manner a strange folk what called dem starless skies home, un only by da grace [']O da nameless gods of da neath did we survive fir as long as we did.' shi preens, eyes alight with covetous bliss. 'But,' shi adds as hir fins slump ever-so-slighty, 'fir da life of me me heart, I'z can't remember da name [']O any of me crew, nor a single face from da roster, or even da name of our ship.'";
				say "     That must be frustrating, you rumble. 'Aya, un ya know what be da worst be, me dragon?' Arlene asks, with an almost pitiable quiver in voice. What? 'I'z don't know how I'z, or me crew came ta be on da island, un no one on the books remembers joining, tis like,' shi hesitates, fists clenched into tight balls till hir knuckles go a pale ivory, 'we was always on dis [']ere rock. Some of us be thinking dat perhaps we might uv even been born here, or conjured by da dem wee automations what be causing all da trouble. But,' shi whispers, while casting a conspiratorial glance towards the main hall, 'I let ya in on a wee secret me heart. I'z don't rightly care what I was in da [']ol days, cause ya see in all does memories da other me was never happy, un dreamed [']O starting over, or letting go un beginning again.' shi hums, as subtle wisps of many colors and none dance along the edges of hir appreciative gaze. 'So instead [']O whining like some green horn on dare first tour, I'z gonna take dis [']second chance['] to make something of meself. Un with yers un da Lady's blissing maybe dis time I make a right proper life here fir me self, and our wee ones.' Arlene simpers, sweeping hir arm about the temple grounds.";
			-- "Status of Pirate island?":
				say "     'Arg I'z was hoping ya wouldn't ask about dat me heart,' Arlene grumbles, nervously rocking on the balls of hir paws. Cocking a scalie set of eyebrows at hir, you ask why. 'Well,' shi mumbles, nervously eyeing the walls to escape your abyssal gaze, 'ya see yer worshipfulness, doe we'z cleared out most [']O da caves me un me [italic type]former crew[roman type] what'z holed up in, dare still be a right many bolt holes the treacherous blighter can scurry too.' Perturbed, you demand to know why this was allowed, and if they pose a threat to you, or the cult. 'Da it weren't fir a lack [']O trying me dragon, but the lava tubes [']ere be stretching on fir miles un dem dragon boyos un scalie hulks be a might be too big ta swim in after dem.' shi grumbles, through a tired little huff. 'Un even if da could me heart, ta tubes be a maze like no other. Doe,' shi grins with a far-too-toothy smirk, 'we did block off most of da old hollows un sealed the blackguards in. Still, a good many more [']O me kind managed to slip away, and scores more feral folk be trawling the shores even now, so it won't be long till someone starts popping out fresh names fir da books.'";
				say "     Huffing, you rightly ask what's to stop them from coming back then, or assaulting your holdings in the future. 'Mayhaps the blighters might entertain da notion me heart, yet day taint got no one ta rally behind, much less da stomach ta take on our wee ones, AND the Lady's servants yar-har-har!' Arlene crows through a heavy belly laugh. 'Doe,' shi rumbles, 'if in I was you yar worshipfulness, I'd stay out [']O da old lair fir now, as dare be more den a few stragglers and squatters milling about in da depths. Mayhaps one day da lads, tikes, un I will head down dare un clean the place out ounce un for all, but fir now the blackguards presence be keeping ta utter beasties away.' Nodding along, you suppose that will have to do, for now. In the future though, you will not be so forgiving if you priestess withholds information from you, no matter how minor it may seem, you growl, flaring your chromatophores a piercing red. 'Aya your regalness, it won't happen again.' Arlene says, giving you a modest bow.";
			-- "Where is the rest of hir crew?":
				say "     'Ah Teuta and Jacquotte? Does two be handling the nitty gritty of getting us supplies un fresh blood, doubt you'll be seeing dem much fir da Seradovah un our wee pig skins got quite da appetite. Course,' shi shrugs, sending a light wobble through hir pillow chest, 'ya can't blame dem, it be hard work mining away down [']ere, un dat is ta say no'thun of carting all da rubble out da moon pool be keeping [']ol Teuta right busy. Un top [']O bring in fresh tools and materials fir da cause.' Fair, you rumble, but what of your other priestess. 'Jacquotte?' Arlene asks, with soft click of hir talons along hir slate floor. You nod. 'Ah, she be handling the recruitment drives on da mainland, not too many pig skins left D's days so sniffing dem be almost as hard as convincing them do ta come. Doe as fortune be having it, da lassy be having a way with word, un da wee ones presence can be a right good help too,' your head priestess smirks.";
				say "     How so? 'Well even dem cantankerous wyverns be giving our lovely sea devils a wide berth, doe,' shi chuffs, 'every couple of moons one [']O da simpler ones takes umbrage at dem, doe day taint nothing compared to our spawn me heart!' Arlene preens, puffing out hir chest as hir paws drift to [if libido of Arlene is 0]the toned hills and hale vallies of hir athletic core[else if libido of Arlene >= 1 and Libido of Arlene < 12]gentle swell of hir hir burgeoning baby bump as hir thoughtlessly pats hir glistening belly[else]tender curves of hir supple eggy tumby as shi traces hir plush navel with obvious delight[end if]. 'As ye can guess, da sight [']O da wee ones flogging da louts be a most...' shi pauses to idly inspect hir attire, 'compelling argument ta join up with us.' Chuckling, you tell hir that you imagine so, though you can't help but express some measure of disappointment in their absence. 'Da, I who knows how ya feel me heart, I miss me loyal mates, doe mayhaps in da moons ta come you might catch dem between trips.' Arlene sighs, as hir head fin seem to sag just a hair.";
				WaitLineBreak;
				say "     Rapping your talon along the floor, you propose that you could simply order them to return for a while instead. 'Aya, ya could me dragon and da lasses would most certainly obliged but with things being as tight as day are around here welll.  ,' your priestess sighs with a pleading look on hir face. Right, belay that for the moment then, in the future though, you hope to hear from them in person, after all, much as you'd like to trust your priestess's word. You rumble, fanning your wings in mild aggravation. You still would prefer to hear from your followers directly when time and circumstances allow. 'Aya me lovely, I'z pass the word along to da girls when'z next day comes ashore,' Arlene says flashing you the two dragon symbol used by your flock.";
			-- "Just chat?":
				say "     '[one of]Oh what do ya do with a Drunken Feral? What do ya do with Drunken Feral early in da the morning? Feed dem to da Slut rats for dinner. Feed dem to da Sluts rats for dinner. Oh way, hey, and up shi rises early in da morning. Shove em up yar cock then cum them over! Shove em up yar cock then cum them over! Oh way, hey, and up shi rises early in da morning,' Arlene hums to hirself[or]Ya know me dragon a few [']O da lasses was thinking of gathering fir whiskey and cigars later, perhaps yar worshipfulness would ta join?' your priestess asks, hopefully[or]Ah ha da cum runs cold, we take our poon and never grow old. Ah ha da lady's code, un hail da mighty rising from da deep! With an incredible tail born from da endless seas!' Arlene sings quietly hir under breath[or]Yar I tell ye now, I tell ya now da Dragon Breeder cums,' your plaything chirps[at random].";
	else:
		say "     [bold type]Warning: this area is built around your character having a full Dragon Breeder body and a pussy, no content will ever be available or accessible without it.[roman type]";

