1	"Flight beckons"	Flight beckons	"[EventConditions_Flight_beckons]"	Grey Abbey Library	2500	2	100

to say EventConditions_Flight_beckons:
	if BodyName of player is "Dragon Breeder" and Player is pure and Cunt Count of Player >= 1 and Energy of Galaxite is 4 and Intelligence of Galaxite >= 1 and scalevalue of Player is 5:
		now CurrentWalkinEvent_ConditionsMet is true;

Flight beckons is a situation.
ResolveFunction of Flight beckons is "[ResolveEvent Flight_beckons]".
Sarea of Flight beckons is "Nowhere".

to say ResolveEvent Flight_beckons:
	say "     Peregrinating about your little bastion of calm amidst the sea of chaos battering the city in preparation of your next foray into the unknown, you feel an odd prickling sensation flickering about the edges of your tendrils as the unnatural sensory cells lining their sucker-laden lengths thrum with activity. Though initially peculiar, as you pour your liminal focus towards these sensory blips, your mind is met with a sudden eclectic mix of emotion flooding through the back of your draconic skull. As a profound feeling of being watched trickles through your awareness alongside notes of... you pause, allowing the sensation to wash over you... familiarity tickle at the back of your mind. You muse, as you continue to go about your day as if nothing were wrong while letting your abyssal senses flow outwards as your exotic tendrils [']ping['] the area around you. In seconds, crude images of the various buildings, ruined cars, omnipresent bits of moldering trash, and cast off clothing shimmer into being in the dark recesses of your minds as if some unseen hand were hurriedly etching away upon some archaic black and white scratch pad. Little stands out to you, beyond the unusually wavey quality of the mental imagery, yet as your otherworldly senses pierce the rooftops and begins to caress the firmament, new images fluttering into being as rough simulacrums of several winged tauric figures swirl about your mind's eye.";
	say "     Focusing upon them, your augmented awareness picks up a number of all-to-familiar features upon them as rough images of swept-back horned heads graced by girthy tendrils, and a sleek aquatic sail running down the length of their hydrodynamic bodies stir something within you. Your spawn, you whisper under your breath as a rush of motherly affection smolders in your breast at the thought of your wild oats returning to you. You hastily flap your wings and leap towards the nearest building with a subsonic crackle as you sink your taloning into the weak concrete surface of some nameless structure, relishing the sensation of their scything edges rending deep gouges into its pathetic surface as you barrel up its side sending a show of brick and mortar behind you as you ascend. Hand over paw, you surge up the many stories of this puny structure propelled forward by mighty flaps of your wings and the unerring bite of your talons till you pull yourself up the grey building's side. Landing with a muted swish, the impact of your paws scatters the ubiquitous grey and black speckled tar used to coat most roofs sending dust and ash flying through the air while bellowing a proud, yet welcoming draconic roar as you scan the clouds for signs of your wayward brood.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     In reply, a trio of brassy bellicose cries reverberate through the area as your descendants swoop down from above like brilliant cobalt comets as they kick up a squall of dust impregnated with aggregate and old weather-worn cigarette butts as they drop to their knees in reverence, intoning as one, 'Nah se sturm slayrak Monah,' as they dip their angular heads to the blacktop in deference to their maker. Bidding them to rise with a loving reptilian chirp, you can't help but admire the sight of the lone female, flanked by a pair your hermaphroditic progeny arrayed before you. Equally as tall as you are, their proportions are closer to the bawdy pirate sharks you encountered some time ago, though their wings appear to be a touch more developed, not to mention larger, as your descendant's can barely tuck them to their sides. Peering along their sinuous [bodydesc of player] lower halves and thick predatory flanks, you're pleasantly surprised to note that your errant brood boast ";
	if Intelligence of Galaxite is 1:
		say "the same slender spaded tail as you.";
	else if Intelligence of Galaxite is 2:
		say "the same manner of subtle seams running along the borders of their tails as yours.";
	say "     Perhaps feeling your appreciative abyssal gaze upon their enhanced figures, the lips of your spawn curl into muted knowing smirks coiling on the edges of their royal blue muzzle as they rise to their full imperial as the middle dragoness and sole female among them says, 'Rosus for our sudden intrusion upon your,' in a respectful, if hesitant cadence as she tucks her paws to her sizable chest and her hitchhiker's thumbs together in effigy of a pair of draconic heads and fans her webbed fingers outwards like wings as she casts her gaze over the abbey and its various inhabitants. 'Ahem, humble territory monah. But we have been sent here with a message from our zast monah, Kai Sunrak.' Cocking a scalie eyebrow in mild confusion at the somewhat unfamiliar terms she quickly adds, 'Our other mother, the Ocean Priestess, Lady Arlene,' though you detect a note of awkwardness in her voice at this correction, why though, you can't be certain. Nevertheless, you nod and bid your dutiful spawn to rely your nascent priestess's message. 'Gah monah,' she says, letting her paws fall to her side. 'It is with great pride,' she beams as her and sister puff out their chest and tails twitch behind them.";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     'That we have come to inform you that the pacification of Pirate Island has completed and with aid of our goddess Tiamat, The Holy Empress of Chromatic Wyrms, Lady of Many Colors and None, Patron of the Lost and the Damned, The Corner Stone of Order, and soon to be saviour of the sphere we have finished laying the groundwork for your temple,' she rumbles reverently, her golden eyes alight with beautiful coldblooded fervor as her sisters to her right says, 'By her will as dedicated by our fruitful zast monah we too have begun scouring the city for worthy human supplicates to worship at your paws,' as shi gestures to the wider city with a sweeping wave of hir wings. 'And,' the left herm chuffs as hir right forepaw drifts to hir feral midriff, 'grow our flight in preparation of your ascension on the eve of the goddess's arrival.' Smirking at the thought of what wonders await you, you ask your brood to take you there then, so you may greet your flock and begin the great work. Though as soon as these words leave your lips, you notice children's luminance eyes dim while they shuffle demurely from side-to-side before the female speaks in a downcast tone. 'R-regrettably vaysun da Kai Monah, the winds of Kyre will not bear you as they do us,' she gulps with a shamefaced look on her regal muzzle. Perturbed, you ask her to elaborate. 'Rosus monah,' she peeps shaking her head, 'but your form, though mighty, is still shackled to the ways of mun and as such you can not fly as we do, for now, or so the hen klovve has said.'"; [Vaysun = vessel]
	say "     Why not just carry you to the island then, you counter. 'Would that we could monah,' the right herm mutters, as shi sheepishly traces hir foretalon along the blacktop, 'but the many beasts of this land and the constructs of the kin da mun vex us at every turn.' shi growls, casting a baneful eye towards the clouds. 'Much as it would please us to bring these insolent gnats to heel in the goddess's name, we are,' the left herm snarls as shi clicks hir barbed fangs, 'forbidden from aggravating the rabble.' Then why not simply escort you over land to the temple grounds, surely that would not draw too much attention? Besides, you can't say a part of you wouldn't mind spending a few minutes to get to know them. 'Zunni zul,' the female says with a sagacious bob of her head as her sucker-laced tendril hair cascades about her regal visage. 'Any other time we would relish the chance to bask in your presence and bring righteous battle to the churls of this sphere honored wyrm maker! Yet,' she pauses as her jaw clenches, 'our duties to the goddess can not be shirked, so for now we return to our nier and continue surveying this city for fresh followers, ol faal hen klovve uth. At least,' she smirks, as her paws briefly drift to her toned scalie middle, 'until our numbers have been expanded.'";
	WaitLineBreak;
	say "     Rumbling in a soft neutral tone, you decide to drop the matter, for the moment at least, as you can sense your progeny will not budge on this, and instead ask for proper directions. Knowledgeable as you may be of the city, along with its surrounding environs, your brood was a touch vague as many minor patches of dirt and rock could easily be called pirate island. After all, it's not like you could [bold type]just travel to The Beach and hunt for a message in a bottle to find out where this pirate island is[roman type] much less stumble onto the grounds, you muse. 'Gah Monah, zinii zul rosus un mey kirre,' the lone female says with a genuine air of contrition as she lowers her eyes and briefly tips her snout to her breast before continuing. 'Far to the southwest,' she rumbles, gesturing towards the beach with a gentle wave of her tail, 'and well past the forgotten shores of Vohr island is a vast cavernous islet that was once home to Kai Sunrak's treacherous crew. Along its [italic type]western[roman type] shore is a [italic type]Quiet Sandbar[roman type] flanked by a number of ancient tidal caverns that lead to a maze of long dead lava tubes and half sunken warrens. Amidst this chaotic web of switchbacks and dead ends, your temple rests snuggly in the warm womb of the earth, along with our many kin,' she preens."; [Of course mother, you speak the truth, please forgive your foolish children.]
	say "     Nodding, you ask how you're supposed to navigate the caverns then. 'Ah, dread not monah, the Seradovah regularly patrols the area, and will guide you to us once you have made landfall,' the right herm chirps, fanning hir wings beside hirself as if making ready to take off. Sounds simple enough, you reply, idly peering over the scattered roof tops towards the bay and wider ocean beyond. 'Indeed monah,' the right herm hums with a respectful bob of hir scalie head, 'may your journey be swift, would that we could accompany you, but,' she rumbles mournfully, 'duty requires us elsewhere,' as hir haunches tense and talons lightly rake the ground beneath hir paws. Sensing they're getting ready to leave, you decide to...";
	LineBreak;
	let Parting_words_Choices be a list of text;
	add "Let them go." to Parting_words_Choices;
	add "Praise them for their dedication to the goddess." to Parting_words_Choices;
	add "Give them a goodbye hug." to Parting_words_Choices;
	let Parting_words_Choice be what the player chooses from Parting_words_Choices;
	if Parting_words_Choice is:
	-- "Let them go.":
		say "     In no mood to dissuade your wild oats from their task, you bid them leave with a regal wave of your dominant arm before you step back and allow them space to take off. 'Our thanks Monah, it has been...' the lone female pauses, her lips curl into an almost smile as beautiful silver hues dance upon her chromatophores, 'good to see you even if only for the moment, mayhaps one day we will have more time speak as Zin kin. Till then Nah se sturm slayrak, mother,' she simpers as she gallops past and leaps into the air, while kicking up a dervish of dust devils behind herself as she soars into the available cloud cover, then vanishes from sight. While her hermaphroditic siblings share a quick yet oddly perplexed look at one another, before hastily bowing to you. 'May your travels lead you to warm sands and gentle tides, honored wyrm maker,' the left herm intones, before bolting into the air and sailing after hir sibling. 'And may the goddess protect you and,' shi glances towards the library, 'your pets who shelter in your grace vaysun da Kai Monah,' the right intersexed dragoness rumbles as shi too darts off the edge of the building and soars into the firmerment.";
		say "     Watching their shadows peter away into the cloud cover, you can't help but feel a note of pride welling in your breast after your all too brief encounter with your brood along with the knowledge that your distant wyrmlings are not only safe, but seem to be following in their sire's paw prints. Perhaps one day soon, you might even meet a few of your few grand wyrms, or great grand wyrmlings, you muse, utterly unable to hide the goofy grin pulling on the edges of your muzzle at thought. But, you ruminate, as you hop down from the roof top using your nascent wings to slow your descent, such fanciful notions will have to wait, for now you need to busy yourself with locating the Quiet Sandbar upon Pirate Island. Then once your tasks there are complete, you can focus on connecting with your expansive brood and make up for lost time.";
		now Flight beckons is resolved;
		now under sea is active;
		increase score by 69;
		increase XP of Player by 50;
		now Perception of Arlene is 1;
	-- "Praise them for their dedication to the goddess.":
		say "     Touched by their dedication to heralding in Tiamat's arrival and hastening your own ascension to mistress of this sphere, you offer your dutiful young the most heartfelt praise for putting the needs of the goddess needs above their own desires. After all, though it pains you to see them go, there is no telling how long this besieged sphere has left before greater monsters than those roaming the streets, or brooding in the dark forgotten place of this world will appear. Once this world is secure though, you look forward to making up for lost time and getting to know your flight properly, you proffer with a warm maternal smile that sets your children's many eyes alight. 'Th-thank you for understanding my wise monah,' the lone female stammers as she quickly kowtows before you as a single scintillating tear stream down the contours of her scalie visage. 'My siblings and I shall look forward to the day we may take our place at your side and revel in the glory of your ascension together!' Her siblings quickly drop to their knees beside her with their heads bowed. 'Indeed great monah, you speak with the wisdom of the goddess as befitting of the vaysun da Kai Monah,' the left herm reverently intones.";
		say "     'Zin sisters, monah's words honor the goddess and our flight, as is proper,' the right herm hums dutifully. 'Gah my clutch mates, but is such wisdom not expected from the vaysun da Kai Monah?' the female simpers proudly. 'Zin,' the others rumble in coldblooded agreement, as the trio of dragonesses return to their full height and fix you with an affectionate look as the female says, 'We shall remember your words, great wyrm maker, and ensure our many siblings hear them so they may draw strength from your example and devotion to the goddess.' Loosing a pleasant draconic chirp, you return a similar sentiment and bid them well on their hunt for more followers. 'Thank you monah, may your niers be fruitful, and foes quake at your passage!' the dragon sisters bellow, pressing their hands to their chest as they work their fingers into the odd two headed dragon symbol once more while flaring their wings out beside themselves. Beaming at their fervor, you casually step back and watch as they launch themselves once more into the cloud line in a loose chevron formation.";
		WaitLineBreak;
		say "     Watching their shadows vanish into the cloud cover, you can't help but feel a note of pride welling in your breast after your all too brief encounter with your brood along with the knowledge that your distant wyrmlings are not only safe, but seem to be following in their sire's paw prints. Perhaps one day soon, you might even meet a few of your few grand wyrms or great grand wyrmlings, you muse, utterly unable to hide the goofy grin pulling on the edges of your muzzle at thought. But, you ruminate, as you hop down from the roof top using your nascent wings to slow your descent, such fanciful notions will have to wait, for now you need to busy yourself with locating the Quiet Sandbar upon Pirate Island. Then once you're task there are complete, you can focus on connecting with your expansive brood and make up for lost time.";
		now Flight beckons is resolved;
		now under sea is active;
		increase score by 69;
		increase XP of Player by 50;
		Increase Dexterity of Arlene by 1;
		now Perception of Arlene is 1;
	-- "Give them a goodbye hug.":
		say "     Unwilling to let your kids leave without a proper goodbye, you hurriedly bid them to wait, if only for a moment. Cocking their heads in shared surprise, your daughters flex their tendril hair or bat their tails in confusion as the female begins, 'Of course monah, what is your-' only to have her words die on her thin cobalt lips as you leap forward then hurriedly wrap your arms about her as you pull her snout to her shoulder as you lovingly nuzzle your muzzle against her. 'M-mother what are you doing?' your daughter stammers as tension briefly flares through her toned draconic body. The warmth of your embrace and a low series of gentle reptilian chirps quickly melts away reticence she may have had as your regal daughter returns your gesture, cooing, 'So warm, what manner of magic is this?' Purring good-naturedly, you platonically run your finger along her beautiful sail, while telling her this is just a simple long overdue hug, nothing more. 'But it feels so... nice like the voice of the goddess singing to me in my dreams.' Tutting, you ask if her other mother has never hugged her before.";
		say "     'Once when shi first weaned us, but this feels different... better,' she rumbles dreamily, though hints of sorrow still flicker through her voice as her paws gingerly glide along your upper back while she melts into your arms. There-there, mommy's got you dear, you simper sweetly, delighting at the simple joy of holding your daughter. Powerful as you may have become, and alluring as Tiamat's promises may be, few things can compare to the sense of love and affection you feel towards young, or the bubbly upwelling of heavenly pride building in your breast at having gifted your children with such beautiful forms. As no matter what the future holds for you, you know on some deep instinctual level your draconic spawn will survive in this flexible world you've found yourself in. 'Th-thank you mon-... mom,' your daughter mews, burying her face all the deeper in your chest. Of course dear, you whisper tilting your snout to one side and planting a single light air kiss on their forehead, then beckon your hybrid progeny to join you with a welcoming maternal wave of your tail.";
		WaitLineBreak;
		say "     'Gah mona-,' the right herm rumbles, lightly shaking hir head, 'er yes mom,' as shi and hir sibling prance up beside you, draping their arms and wings over you, and their sister as they snuggle their angular muzzles along your shoulders. Their warm and effervescent affection cascades over you while you lightly pat their powerful lower halves with your forepaws in a mix of admiration for your imperial young's impressive physique and profound pride at siring such paragons of draconic perfection. 'Ah you're right sister, this feels so... good,' the left herm murmurs as shi platonically pats your flanks with hir forelimbs. 'Zin I have had no idea this feeling existed till now,' the right herm mewls dreamily. Perturbed, you rightly ask why not? Surely shi must have mates, if not clutches of hir own? 'Ga-, er yes mother, but our lot is to serve as the five heads commands!' shi rumbles with a deep feverous tenor, though you can hear a slight, almost resentful, crack in hir voice as shi continues. 'And time spent coddling the hatchlings is time that could have been spent searching for more followers, yet to deny my young this feels wrong. Ah, apologies mother, I do not mean to blaspheme against our patron and saviour,' shi adds with a shameful look in hir eyes.'";
		say "     Clicking your teeth, you plant a light peck on hir forehead and tell there is no shame or heresy to be found in wishing to spend time with hir clutches as the bonds between parent and child are almost as important as those between the goddess and them. 'I-I had not considered that, I will remember the next time I see my daughters,' the right herm says thoughtfully as hir paw drifts to hir hale midriff. 'And we shall pass on your words to our siblings and progeny as well, mother,' the left herm hums, fixing you with an attentive stare. Positively beaming with maternal glee, you reach out and ruffle your lovely hybrid child's tentacle hair, while telling hir, and hir sibling, how happy you are to hear that. You all have a hard road ahead of you, but together, the journey could be made easier. 'Zinii zul,' they murmur in union as your trio of lovely daughters give you one last group squeeze before disentangling themselves from you.";
		WaitLineBreak;
		say "     'But we dally here too long, still, thank you for your counsel, mother,' the lone female rumbles, nodding her head respectfully at you before trotting over to the edge of the roof, leaping into the air, then sailing towards the cloud banks. 'May we meet again soon upon the hallowed grounds of your temple,' the left herm intones, briefly clutching hir paws to hir breast, before taking wing after hir sibling. 'Indeed,' the right herm hums, nodding towards the shrinking images of hir siblings, 'I look forward to the day that I may introduce you to my own brood.' Smirking, you tell her you can't wait to meet them, and the rest of your flight. 'They will be happy to hear this mother, till then, farewell!' shi roars as shi sprints after hir clutch mates then hurls hirself off the ledge and hurriedly soars beside them as they sail towards the heavens in a loose chevron formation.";
		say "     Watching their shadows peter away into the cloud cover, you can't help but feel a note of pride welling in your breast after your all too brief encounter with your brood along with the knowledge that your distant wyrmlings are not only safe, but seem to be following in their sire's paw prints. Perhaps one day soon, you might even meet a few of your few grand wyrms, or great grand wyrmlings, you muse, utterly unable to hide the goofy grin pulling on the edges of your muzzle at thought. But, you ruminate, as you hop down from the roof top using your nascent wings to slow your descent, such fanciful notions will have to wait, for now you need to busy yourself with locating the Quiet Sandbar upon Pirate Island. Then once your tasks there are complete, you can focus on connecting with your expansive brood and make up for lost time.";
		now Flight beckons is resolved;
		now under sea is active;
		increase score by 69;
		increase XP of Player by 50;
		increase Strength of Arlene by 1;
		now Perception of Arlene is 1;


